# PH-ML stub-then-implement

Stubs are **Wave/step 1 only** within the same battle plan / PR series — never the final deliverable for a WP marked **implement** in [PH-ML-GPU-battle-plan.md](../../docs/game-dev/PH-ML-GPU-battle-plan.md).

## Same PR / branch requirements

Every stub commit or stub-heavy PR on `feat/ph-ml-gpu-swarm` (or a single-WP branch) must include **before merge**:

| Artifact | Content |
|----------|---------|
| **Stub→Real table** | In the release note: stub behavior \| real behavior \| verification command |
| **Tracker row** | `stub` → `in_progress` → `done` (or `blocked` + hardware/dependency reason) — never leave at `stub` when WP is implement-tier |

## Forbidden exit states

- Marking WP **done** in [PH-ML-GPU-execution-tracker.md](../../docs/game-dev/PH-ML-GPU-execution-tracker.md) while only returning constants, fake `gpu_timing_ns`, or `return -1` with no documented follow-up commit / blocker.
- `N/A` timing in bench JSON **without** a release-note row explaining the next WP that removes `N/A`.
- Closing implement WPs with only RFC text when the battle plan §5 proof gate names `lic check` or a bench id.

## Allowed stub patterns (honest)

- `N/A` / `blocked` in bench JSON and TOML when no GPU hardware (see ph-ml-gpu-honesty in lic `.cursor/rules/`).
- Compile-only smokes (`compile_ok`, `compile_fail` with `expected_substr`).
- RFC / design docs (Wave 5 style) with tracker `blocked` or `partial`, not `done`.
- Host launch status `1` (emit stub) or `0` (CPU/SPIR-V validation path) **without** claiming GPU nanoseconds.

## Same-plan wiring rule

If you add `*_stub.li`, `*_stub.c`, or `workload_class = "stub"`:

- The **next commit on the same branch** must replace or wire real behavior, **or**
- Add an explicit battle-plan subsection + tracker `blocked` with dependency (Vulkan lavapipe, ROCm CI, WP-ML-13 `tensor`, etc.).

